# React & Frontend Skills (MANDATORY)

**RULE: When this rule triggers (any .jsx/.tsx file), you MUST read the skills below BEFORE writing code. Read them in order. Do NOT skip any.**

## 1. Design System — UI/UX Pro Max (REQUIRED for new components/pages)

**Path**: `~/.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` — Read this file NOW.

Before writing any new component or page, generate a design system first:

```bash
python3 ~/.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product keywords>" --design-system
```

Use domain searches for specifics:
- `--domain style` for UI styles (glassmorphism, minimalism, etc.)
- `--domain typography` for font pairings
- `--domain color` for palettes
- `--domain ux` for interaction best practices
- `--stack react` for React-specific guidelines

## 2. Frontend Design Quality (REQUIRED for all UI work)

**Path**: `~/.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` — Read this file NOW.

Enforces:
- Bold, distinctive aesthetic direction (no generic AI slop)
- Intentional typography (no default Inter/Arial/Roboto)
- Cohesive color themes with CSS variables
- Meaningful animations and micro-interactions
- Unexpected layouts, spatial composition, visual depth

## 3. React Performance — Vercel Best Practices (REQUIRED for all React code)

**Path**: `~/.cursor/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/SKILL.md` — Read this file NOW.

57 rules across 8 categories, prioritized by impact:
1. **CRITICAL**: Eliminate waterfalls (`async-parallel`, `async-defer-await`)
2. **CRITICAL**: Bundle size (`bundle-barrel-imports`, `bundle-dynamic-imports`)
3. **HIGH**: Server-side performance (`server-cache-react`, `server-parallel-fetching`)
4. **MEDIUM**: Re-render optimization (`rerender-memo`, `rerender-derived-state`)

Read individual rule files for code examples: `~/.cursor/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/<rule-name>.md`

## 4. Web Interface Guidelines (for reviews/audits)

**Path**: `~/.cursor/skills/web-design-guidelines/SKILL.md` — Read this file when reviewing/auditing UI.

Use when reviewing or auditing existing UI. Fetches latest guidelines from Vercel and checks compliance.

## Workflow

1. **New page/component**: Read skills #1 + #2 → generate design system → implement with #3 performance rules
2. **Editing existing**: Read skill #3 → apply performance patterns → check #2 for design quality
3. **Reviewing/auditing**: Read skill #4 → run compliance check against web interface guidelines

## Pre-Delivery Checklist

Before completing any React UI work:
- [ ] No emojis as icons (use SVG: Heroicons, Lucide)
- [ ] All clickable elements have `cursor-pointer`
- [ ] Hover states provide visual feedback (150-300ms transitions)
- [ ] Light/dark mode text contrast meets 4.5:1 minimum
- [ ] Responsive at 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
- [ ] No horizontal scroll on mobile
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- [ ] Form inputs have labels, images have alt text
